intro: Ficinia ambigua, commonly known as the ambiguous fig, is a flowering plant native to the Pacific Islands. It belongs to the Moraceae family, which includes other fig species. The plant produces small, greenish flowers that are clustered in dense inflorescences. Its leaves are alternate, simple, and often have a rough texture. Ficinia ambigua is typically found in moist, coastal habitats and is adapted to tropical and subtropical climates.
